uniol.apt.analysis.coverability

Class CoverabilityGraphNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • uniol.apt.analysis.coverability.CoverabilityGraphNode

  • public class CoverabilityGraphNode
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a node in a coverability graph. A node is labeled with a marking which identifies it uniquely and has a firing sequence with which it can be reached from the initial marking of the underlying Petri net. Additionally, the postset of the node is available.
    Author:
    Uli Schlachter

      • getFiringSequenceFromCoveredNode

        public java.util.List<Transition> getFiringSequenceFromCoveredNode()
        Get the firing sequence which reaches this node from the covered node, or null. This function can be used together with getFiringSequence to describe a way to generate tokens in the Petri net. If the return value is not null, the sequence returned from this function can be fired in an infinite loop in the marking described by getCoveredNode.getMarking(), and will increase the number of token in the Petri net.
        Returns:
        The firing sequence.
        See Also:
        getCoveredNode, getFiringSequence
